class Solution {
    public int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
        int sum = 0;
        boolean isPositive = true;
        while (n > 0) {
            int digit = n % 10;
            sum += isPositive ? digit : -digit;
            isPositive = !isPositive;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return isPositive ? -sum : sum;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each digit of the input number from right to left, maintaining a running sum with alternating signs. It correctly adjusts the final sum based on whether the number of digits is odd or even.
